State MSM Profile: Michigan

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Michigan

An estimated 113,860 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Michigan in 2013, representing 2.5% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 3,671,762 adult men of Michigan, 3.1% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Michigan resided in central counties of large metropolitan areas (36.6%). Including both central and fringe counties, 70.3% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Michigan, 2013

MSM in Michigan Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Michigan, Wayne County had the largest population of MSM at 30,160, representing 26.5% of all MSM in the state. Kent County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Michigan at 5.3%. This was greater than the percentage for Michigan as a whole, which was 3.1% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Michigan Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Detroit-Warren-Dearborn Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Detroit-Warren-Dearborn MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Michigan at 63,505, or 55.8% of all MSM in the state. Of the 1,558,923 adult men in Detroit-Warren-Dearborn, an estimated 4.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.

South Bend-Mishawaka Metropolitan Statistical Area

The South Bend-Mishawaka MSA overlaps two states: Indiana and Michigan. The Michigan portion of the MSA had 303 MSM, or 0.3% of all MSM in the state and 13.4% of the 2,254 MSM in the MSA. Of 19,935 adult men in the Michigan part of South Bend-Mishawaka, 1.5% were MSM. This was less than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 1.9% of adult men (2,254 out of 116,031).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
